Framework design philosophy:
- Errors are learning opportunities in workshops
- Rich context helps students debug independently
- Typed errors prevent string comparison bugs
- Suggestions guide students to solutions

Production considerations:
- Stack traces essential for agent debugging
- Retry logic teaches resilience patterns
- JSON output integrates with observability
- Error categories mirror real-world failures

Workshop-specific features:
- Platform-aware suggestions (e.g., AWS auth differs on Windows)
- Retryable flag teaches transient vs permanent failures
- Cost errors highlight real-world constraints
- Context accumulation shows debugging techniques

Testing strategy:
- Unit tests cover all error types
- Integration tests verify retry logic
- Benchmarks ensure error creation is cheap
